cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper focuses on the security aspects of WebAssembly and proposes a taint tracking system to monitor the flow of sensitive data through the application. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the implementation of a virtual machine and the use of JavaScript, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper mentions the performance benefits of WebAssembly, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
